00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:08.300
Banana Bread

00:00:08.300 --> 00:00:13.700
Equipment: 23 cm rectangle cake pan

00:00:13.700 --> 00:00:15.000
Ingredients

00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:18.900
250 g (1¾ cups) flour

00:00:18.900 --> 00:00:22.100
170 g (¾ cup) sugar

00:00:22.100 --> 00:00:24.400
1 tsp baking powder

00:00:24.400 --> 00:00:27.100
¼ tsp baking soda

00:00:27.100 --> 00:00:29.500
1 tsp ground cinnamon

00:00:29.500 --> 00:00:31.400
¼ tsp salt

00:00:31.400 --> 00:00:32.600
2 eggs

00:00:32.600 --> 00:00:34.900
1 tsp vanilla extract

00:00:34.900 --> 00:00:38.300
115 g (½ cup) melted butter 

00:00:38.300 --> 00:00:40.700
3 ripe bananas, mashed

00:00:40.700 --> 00:00:43.000
100 g (1 cup) walnuts, chopped

00:00:43.000 --> 00:00:44.500
Directions

00:00:44.500 --> 00:00:51.500
Preheat oven to 180°C and butter the cake pan.

00:00:51.500 --> 00:01:03.000
In a large bowl, sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon

00:01:03.000 --> 00:01:09.500
then add the sugar and whisk everything together to combine.

00:01:09.500 --> 00:01:25.000
In another bowl, whisk the eggs with the vanilla then add the banana and melted butter

00:01:25.000 --> 00:01:27.400
and whisk everything together until well combined.

00:01:27.400 --> 00:01:30.600
Pour the egg and banana mixture into the flour

00:01:30.600 --> 00:01:43.000
and use a rubber spatula to fold everything together making sure no lumps of flour are left.

00:01:43.000 --> 00:01:55.300
Fold the walnuts into the batter then transfer into the cake pan and spread evenly.

00:01:55.300 --> 00:01:59.000
Bake in the preheated oven for about 1 hour.

00:01:59.000 --> 00:02:01.000
Let it cool a little before serving.

